Class FibonacciCalculator

  • java.lang.Object
    • calculators.FibonacciCalculator

    RecursiveFibonacciCalculator
    public class FibonacciCalculator
extends java.lang.Object
implements Calculators
    Calculator used to compute a Fibonacci sequence a number of times determined by the user in an iterative fashion.

    Andrew McKay

    • Constructor Detail

      • FibonacciCalculator

        public FibonacciCalculator​(long fValue)
        Create a new FibonacciCalculator to execute the sequence a number of times equal to fValue. The result of the sequence will be zero until the calculate() method is ran.
        Parameters:
        fValue - long integer that determines the number of times the Fibonacci sequence is executed.
